Grape Juice: The Explanation (lyrics included)
description:
A lot of people in Domestic Violence relationships have often experienced some form of abuse in their lifetime, so when they find themself in this type of relationship, others are confused on why they stay or why they don’t fight back. 
A lot of times, these victims are already use to it. Some don’t know how to fight back or are so scared things may get worse if they do fight back. 
The most you can do is let these victims know that they have someone to confide in and that they are loved. 
We aren’t children anymore, so things we had to live with then, we don’t have to accept now. We are the only ones who can protect our inner child. 
Some have to be told or reminded of what love is because people these days are defining love in their own way. 
Just because someone says they love you, doesn’t mean they know how to. Everyone’s perception of love is different because we are all taught to love differently. 
It’s a matter of what your perception of love is and it is very dependent on what you will allow. 
How do you want to be loved? 
Loved like Grape Juice or loved like Wine?

-Call 800-799-7233 to the Domestic Violence hotline if you need someone to vent to or even if you’re ready to help yourself.

​⁠​⁠@CruzControlRadio ​⁠​⁠@K100Radio ​⁠​⁠@TheKhaliseum ​⁠​⁠@DrekaGatesTV ​⁠​⁠@kiarathesoulchild8376 ​⁠@MakinItMag

When you experience love like Wine, it’s genuine, it’s pure, it’s rich in taste and it makes you want some more… It gives you that buzz that makes you feel like you’ve found your Nirvana..

title: Billie Eilish – Wildflower | Cover by Rielle 🌼🎙#wildflower #cover #billieeilish
description:
𝐁𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐢𝐞 𝐄𝐢𝐥𝐢𝐬𝐡 – 𝐖𝐢𝐥𝐝𝐟𝐥𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫 | 𝐂𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫 𝐛𝐲 𝐑𝐢𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐞 🌼🎙️
This cover of “Wildflower” is inspired by Billie Eilish’s ability to weave raw emotion into her music. In this heartfelt and cinematic interpretation, 𝐑𝐢𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐞 delivers the song with a softness and vulnerability that brings every lyric to life.

Each moment in her performance feels like stepping into memories filled with love, loss, and quiet reflection — a reminder of the fears, doubts, and hopes we all carry.

As the emotion unfolds, 𝐑𝐢𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐞 explores the parts of the past we try to forget — the broken pieces, the what-ifs, the tears we never mention. Her voice holds the weight of heartbreak while gently learning to release it.

This cover becomes a journey of healing, rediscovery, and finding the strength to move forward.

It reminds us that even in our darkest moments, there is a wildflower within each of us — waiting to rise, breathe, and bloom again.

VOICE ENY 

Born and raised in Brooklyn, New York, Voice Eny grew up balancing multiple passions—from excelling in boxing and basketball to ultimately finding his true calling in music.
“I chose to do music because it was the only thing that seemed right at a point in my life,” he reflects. That clarity fueled his journey, and three years later, in 2023, he broke through with the release of his hit single "Let’s Be For Real." The track gained momentum on Apple Music and connected with listeners across the globe—from the U.S. and UK to Haiti, Jamaica, and Africa.
Industry insiders have taken notice, praising his distinctive sound and emotionally resonant lyrics. With growing buzz and a dedicated fanbase, many are calling Voice Eny one of NYC’s next breakout artists.
As anticipation builds, fans are left wondering—will a new album drop soon? More collaborations? One thing’s for sure: Voice Eny is just getting started.
 / voice-eny  



Adisyn Mahree is a Bronx-born Afro-Latina artist and the first female to both rap and sing fluently in Spanish and English. Her music fuses sultry R&B, rhythmic rap, and Latin-infused melodies into a sound that is both timeless and innovative. With a voice that captivates and lyrics that resonate, she brings raw emotion and undeniable energy to every track.
Her journey in music began at just six years old, performing in talent shows and pageants before evolving into a dynamic recording artist. Her single Maybach, now available on all streaming platforms, gained citywide recognition when it was played twice on Hot 97, one of New York’s most influential hip-hop stations.
As she continues to carve her path in the industry, Adisyn Mahree blends culture and creativity to create a fresh and unforgettable musical experience. With a growing fan base and an evolving sound, she is poised to make a lasting impact.
 / adisyn-mahree  


Prince Dale is a multi-faceted and ambitious artist, who has been captivating audiences since 2010. Prince Dale has demonstrated his versatility and growth through tracks like “Now Go,” “Your Way,” “Mess Around,” and his latest, “Depression Expression.” These songs showcase his evolving artistry and ability to connect with listeners on a profound level.
Now signed with Luv Man Records, Prince Dale is poised to reach new heights in his career. His music is available on major streaming platforms, including Apple Music and Spotify, allowing a growing audience to experience his unique sound. With more projects on the horizon, Prince Dale continues to push boundaries and attract listeners with his authentic storytelling and dynamic performances.

title: Jessiēque - THE FEAR OF INTIMACY (Official Music Video)
description:
Shot by: Matt Barnes

Instagram: @callhimjessieque
TikTok: @callhimjessieque
Twitter/X: @calljessieque

The Fear of Intimacy” is a song about pulling someone close while pushing them away, fighting the urge to connect, and navigating the vulnerability that love demands. This track dives into emotional walls, relationship anxiety, trauma, and the internal battles that make closeness feel impossible. If you’ve ever loved deeply but feared losing yourself—or being hurt—this one’s for you.

If you like artists such as Billie Eilish, The Weeknd, Hozier, Lana Del Rey, Joji, or Frank Ocean…you might connect with the vibe of this track.

Thank you for watching and supporting my music. If this song spoke to you, please leave a comment and share your experience. It means more than you know. ❤️
Don’t forget to like, subscribe, and hit the bell for more music.

title: YR.Rollie - FADEAWAY (OFFICIAL MUSIC VIDEO
description:
HEY WHAT UP! Rollie here. fadeaway is a cool mid-tempo melodic track and it talks about my life and the changes I had to make for me to reach success. sometimes even the people closest to you could be your downfall. sometimes we could be our own downfall. for us to get the things we want out of life we have to fade away from the past. people that won't benefit you and your own habits and ways that could be holding you back. It's time for change, it's time to level up and go harder for our dreams and goals .

please, leave a comment, like, and share this video 
love!

title: YR.Rollie - Shine Light (Official music video)
description:
This music video is filled with deep emotion and passion to succeed in my dreams and goals . Despite of the negativity that goes on around me. Dealing with fake friends, unsupportive family, rocky relationships, and loosing loved ones that are close to me. In this video you will hear and see me pour my soul out in every bar and lyric that comes out of my mouth. My melodic tone and vocals will feel your ears and soul with pure passion and pain from the core of my deepest and darkest moments to the point you my want to shed a tear because of how relatable it could be to most people. But through all the heartache and pain there is LIGHT  and we have to keep striving, praying, and grinding. Working hard to get through because we maybe down in the dark today but tomorrow we will all SHINE LIGHT #toosiitypebeat #rodwave #roddyricch #hiphopartist #lastdayonearth #lifequotes 



(Shine Light) (Brighter days) (light in the sky) ( let your light shine) (shine bright) (Hard times) (pain) (fake love) (love you) I( love to shine my light) (shine your light) #music #prayer #rap

On the day of the long awaited 'Warrior Mentality Mixtape' release, D.Chamberz brings you a visual to this epic song with an epic Biggie sample. The mixtape, hosted by DJ Messiah, will be released exclusively on http://www.datpiff.com/mixtapes-detail.php?id=359108 on 6/26/12 @ 7PM.

The arrival of D.Chamberz' Warrior Mentality Mixtape coincides with his appearance on the new FuseTv Reality series, Behind the Unsigned. title: HOT97 LIVE INTERVIEW WITH @SoDrewski  @VoiceEny  x @PrinceDaleMusic  @AdisynMahree
description:
HOT97 LIVE INTERVIEW WITH ⁨@SoDrewski⁩    ⁨@VoiceEny⁩  x  ⁨@PrinceDaleMusic⁩  @AdisynMahree https://www.luvmanrecords.com/

VOICE ENY 

Born and raised in Brooklyn, New York, Voice Eny grew up balancing multiple passions—from excelling in boxing and basketball to ultimately finding his true calling in music.
“I chose to do music because it was the only thing that seemed right at a point in my life,” he reflects. That clarity fueled his journey, and three years later, in 2023, he broke through with the release of his hit single "Let’s Be For Real." The track gained momentum on Apple Music and connected with listeners across the globe—from the U.S. and UK to Haiti, Jamaica, and Africa.
Industry insiders have taken notice, praising his distinctive sound and emotionally resonant lyrics. With growing buzz and a dedicated fanbase, many are calling Voice Eny one of NYC’s next breakout artists.
As anticipation builds, fans are left wondering—will a new album drop soon? More collaborations? One thing’s for sure: Voice Eny is just getting started.
https://music.apple.com/us/artist/voice-eny/1667311937



Adisyn Mahree is a Bronx-born Afro-Latina artist and the first female to both rap and sing fluently in Spanish and English. Her music fuses sultry R&B, rhythmic rap, and Latin-infused melodies into a sound that is both timeless and innovative. With a voice that captivates and lyrics that resonate, she brings raw emotion and undeniable energy to every track.
Her journey in music began at just six years old, performing in talent shows and pageants before evolving into a dynamic recording artist. Her single Maybach, now available on all streaming platforms, gained citywide recognition when it was played twice on Hot 97, one of New York’s most influential hip-hop stations.
As she continues to carve her path in the industry, Adisyn Mahree blends culture and creativity to create a fresh and unforgettable musical experience. With a growing fan base and an evolving sound, she is poised to make a lasting impact.
https://music.apple.com/us/artist/adisyn-mahree/1800603168


Prince Dale is a multi-faceted and ambitious artist, who has been captivating audiences since 2010. Prince Dale has demonstrated his versatility and growth through tracks like “Now Go,” “Your Way,” “Mess Around,” and his latest, “Depression Expression.” These songs showcase his evolving artistry and ability to connect with listeners on a profound level.
Now signed with Luv Man Records, Prince Dale is poised to reach new heights in his career. His music is available on major streaming platforms, including Apple Music and Spotify, allowing a growing audience to experience his unique sound. With more projects on the horizon, Prince Dale continues to push boundaries and attract listeners with his authentic storytelling and dynamic performances.
https://music.apple.com/us/artist/prince-dale/597629929

title: Lil JJ World - Thank You ( Official Music Video ) #viral #explore #hiphop #motherslove #kids #love
description:
Lil JJ is an upcoming star born to shine bright. Born and raised in Baltimore, Maryland, Jordan Jones Jr AKA Lil JJ has been in love with music since an early age. Lil JJ has shown as much confidence and determination as many artists late in their careers. Inspired by his older cousin Beezy, Lil JJ started showing his strong passion for music and his family has given their full support. Lil JJ breaks away from the general stereotypes of rappers, and has proven to be a role model for others his age. An honor student and a versatile athlete, at 11 years old he has maintained consistently high grades and plays over 4 sports all year round. A few of the artists that inspire Lil JJ include Ybs Skola, Drake, Lil Baby, and of course his cousin Beezy. The release of his first single "Yea Yea" has had a great reception, with response from Power 105.1's DJ Envy, Music Exec Tay Kelly, and others in the music industry. While music is his passion, Lil JJ also dreams of becoming an actor as well as the face of brands. We believe he has the capacity to be a role model for others his age, and inspire others to pursue their dreams as well.

title: Stella Standingbear  - Home Runs (Official Music Video)
description:
In honor of Native American Heritage Month and MMIW/MMIP, Stella Standingbear releases the "Home Runs" Official Music Video.

Listen to Home Runs now: https://fanlink.to/homeruns
Connect with her on social media: https://linktr.ee/stellastandingbear

Website: https://www.stellastandingbear.com
MMIW Websites: https://mmiwusa.org/ https://www.nativewomenswilderness.or...

A red hand over the mouth has become the symbol of a growing movement, the MMIW movement. It stands for all the missing sisters whose voices are not heard. It stands for the silence of the media and law enforcement amid this crisis. Red is known to be the only color spirits see. It is hoped that by wearing red, we can call back the missing spirits of our women, children, and people so we can lay them to rest.

In the United States, 40% of the women sold into sex trafficking are Native American. This is an understatement considering many of these cases are never reported... 

No more missing or murdered indigenous women, girls, or relatives. #MMIW #MMIP #StillStanding

Smoked Chuck roast - Butter knife shawty Dirty fries. #sweetpotatofries #chuckroast
description:
The Story Behind Loaded Sweet Potato Waffle Fries
It all began when I met my good friend and mentor Daniel Hernandez from The Brisket Shoppe down in Tampa, Florida. We crossed paths in Charleston, South Carolina, cooking at the Holy Smokes BBQ Festival. From the moment we met, there was mutual respect — two pitmasters connecting over smoke, fire, and the love of feeding people.
At the time, I didn’t know Danny was putting together something special — his own charity event called BBQ Love Fest, held at Perry Harvey Park in Downtown Tampa on November 18, 2023. This wasn’t just another cookout; it was a cooking-for-a-cureevent benefiting FARA, Operation BBQ Relief, and the Special Operations Memorial Foundation. When Danny called and told me about it, I didn’t hesitate — I told him to count me in.
As the event drew closer, I started thinking hard about what to cook. Everyone was going to bring the classics — brisket, ribs, pork belly, whole hogs, chicken, picanha — all the heavy hitters. But I wanted to stand out, to bring something that represented Georgia BBQ and my Atlanta roots. That’s when it hit me: stick to what the people love about your food. My pulled beef has always been a top seller, so that became the foundation.
When I told Danny my plan, he loved it — but then he threw me a curveball that changed everything.He said, “What if you loaded that pulled beef on top of some sweet potato fries with a special gravy — like a BBQ poutine?”
That was it. The idea clicked instantly. I took that suggestion and ran with it, creating a rich, smoky, slightly sweet sauce that tied it all together. And since I was born at Grady Hospital in Atlanta, I decided to name the sauce Grady Gravy — a nod to my roots and the city that shaped my cooking.
Now, these fries have become one of my number one sellers — a crowd favorite that started as a conversation between friends and turned into a dish that represents community, creativity, and Georgia pride.

🔥Loaded Sweet Potato Waffle Fries Recipe🔥
Tagline: Waffle-cut sweet potato fries piled high with 18-hour smoked chuck roast, finished with our signature Grady Gravy Poutine Sauce.
Ingredients
For the Fries
* 1 bag waffle-cut sweet potato fries
* 2 tbsp vegetable oil
* Sea salt to taste
For the Pulled Beef
* 3–4 lbs chuck roast
* 2 tbsp coarse salt
* 1 tbsp black pepper
* 1 tbsp garlic powder
* 1 tbsp onion powder
* 1 cup beef broth
* ½ cup BBQ sauce
For the Grady Gravy (BBQ Poutine Sauce)
* 2 tbsp butter
* 2 tbsp flour
* 1 cup beef stock
* ¼ cup BBQ sauce
* 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce
* Salt and pepper to taste
Optional Toppings
* Shredded cheese curds or mozzarella
* Chopped green onions
* Pickled jalapeños

Instructions
1. Smoke the Chuck RoastSeason the roast with salt, pepper, garlic, and onion powder. Smoke low and slow at 250°F for about 8–10 hours, or until tender. Shred and mix with a touch of BBQ sauce and beef broth to keep it juicy.
2. Prepare the FriesCook the waffle-cut sweet potato fries according to package directions until crispy. Lightly salt and set aside.
3. Make the Grady GravyIn a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Whisk in flour to create a roux and cook until golden. Slowly add beef stock while stirring, then mix in BBQ sauce and Worcestershire. Simmer until thick and glossy. Season to taste.
4. Assemble the Dish
    * Lay the crispy fries on a platter.
    * Pile on the pulled beef.
    * Generously drizzle with Grady Gravy.
    * Top with cheese curds, green onions, or pickled jalapeños if desired.

Final Thoughts
Loaded Sweet Potato Waffle Fries aren’t just a dish — they’re a story of friendship, mentorship, and the love of barbecue that brings people together. From Tampa to Atlanta, from the pits of Holy Smokes to BBQ Love Fest, this recipe celebrates collaboration and the power of community through food.

When one of your BBQ and fellow #teamburchbarrel besties comes to town and brings his Sweet Cherry Rub…you make Cherry Coma…errrrr uhhhhh Cherry Cola wings on the @burchbarrel.

•Get 3/4 of the Burch Barrel fire basket going with coals and cherry wood. Raise the basket to full height. 

Prepare the Cherry Cola Sauce:
3 cups Cherry Cola
1/3 cup honey
1 cup loose brown sugar
1/3 cup apple cider vinegar
1/2 cup ketchup
1 Tbsp crushed red pepper flakes
Zest of lime
1 split pepper; we went red fresno

•Bring to a boil on the Burch Barrel
•Simmer and reduce by half
•Add 1 Tbsp cornstarch
•Immersion blend until smooth
•Mount with 1 Tbsp butter

While the sauce reduces:
•Liberally coat wings with @butter_knife_shawty @georgia_boy_rubs Sweet Cherry Rub and kosher salt
•Place on the grill grates, twist to engage the grate in the lid and raise to cook wings @375 degrees
•Rotate wings halfway through cook for even color on both sides 
•Cook to internal temp of 180

Now, for the best part of the recipe, liberally coat the wings in the Cherry Cola sauce, find yourself a friend and do the Shawty shake to fully cover the wings!  Top with lime zest for color and a fresh burst of citrus and get to eating!!! 

Be sure to like, share and follow @teammeatcoma and @butterknifeshawty for more fun and exciting recipes, collabs and maybe even a little more 💃 🕺!!

description:

Check out this exclusive freestyle by D.Chamberz inspired by the show.

The arrival of D.Chamberz' Warrior Mentality Mixtape in June coincides with his appearance on the new FuseTv Reality series, Behind the Unsigned. The show will cover the lives of nine unsigned artists in the music industry, to take a look at what it really means to be 'Behind the Scenes' of the 'Unsigned' artists day-to-day life. The series is scheduled to air on FuseTV's website (FuseTv.com) in June 2012 (after being rescheduled from March), and shortly after to your 'small screen' on the FuseTV Channel (check your local listings).

The song, produced by Jay Quet, is a throwback sounding beat, which is the making of an instant classic, and D.Chamberz made sure to make it so.

title: Why I'm breaking up with America and living the “American Dream” | DeeVine Message
description:
♡ WELCOME [BACK]. It’s been almost 9 months since I packed my sht and left America to start my journey of effortless living abroad. The beginning of my journey started in Mexico and since being here It’s been a lot easier for me to shift my perspective when it comes to the life I desire to live and the action steps needed for me to start living that life now and not during retirement. America has brainwashed many of us into believing that we have to go to college, pursue a career in corporate for 30+ years until we retire, then spend our last days regretting the life we lived and wishing we had followed our dreams a lot sooner. If these past few years haven’t taught us anything, it has taught us that we can live an abundant life right now in the present. Let’s talk about what that looks like for me. Have you ever considered living abroad? If so, where and how are you currently living effortlessly?

If you don’t know … I’m Alantra, the HOTTEST up and coming artist representing for all the hustling Yedda Mamis! New videos dropping weekly, so subscribe to join the tribe and follow me on my journey to stardom!
